Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deletePartition(25.10)                                  deletePartition(25.10)

Name
       deletePartition - Deletes the specified partition

Syntax
       deletePartition

       [-help]

       { <partition_name> | -all | -nested | -non_leaf }

       [-undo_tcl_file <file_name> [-non_leaf ]]

       Deletes the specified partition.

       Note: The Hinst retains the fence property.

Parameters
       -all   Deletes all partitions.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each deletePartition parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man deletePartition.

       -nested
              Deletes all nested partitions in the design.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -non_leaf
              Deletes all non-leaf partitions in the design.

              Note: It saves the information of the deleted  partitions  in  a
              tcl  file,  so  that the same can be used to restore the deleted
              partitions.

              For example, in the diagram below, all the  non-leaf  partitions
              (marked  in yellow) must be deleted and dumped in a tcl file for
              restoration purpose later on.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       <partition_name>
              Specifies the name of the partition to delete.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -undo_tcl_file <file_name>
              Specifies the file that can be sourced to undo deletion of  par-
              titions.

              With  this  parameter, the partition definition of the partition
              being deleted is written to the specified file.  Later,  if  re-
              quired, this file can be sourced to bring back the partition de-
              finition.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
              * The following command deletes the partition p1.

                deletePartition p1

              * The  following command writes the partition definition of par-
                tition p1 in file ptn.tcl and then deletes it.

                deletePartition p1 -undo_tcl_file ptn.tcl

Related Information
              * partition

              * definePartition

              * Partitioning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

